<paragraph blockId="52.[159,1116,1070,1477]" pageId="52" pageNumber="3009">
<emphasis box="[199,261,1326,1350]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="3009">Note.</emphasis>
Recent molecular studies by 
<bibRefCitation author="DRAISMA, S. G. A. &amp; PRUD'HOMME VAN REINE, W. F. &amp; STAM, W. T. &amp; OLSEN, J. L." box="[617,869,1325,1350]" pageId="52" pageNumber="3009" pagination="586 - 603" refId="ref33892" refString="DRAISMA, S. G. A., PRUD'HOMME VAN REINE, W. F., STAM, W. T. and OLSEN, J. L., 2001, A reassessment of phylogenetic relationships within the Phaeophyceae based on Rubisco Large Subunit and Ribosomal DNA sequences, Journal of Phycology, 37, 586 - 603." type="journal article" year="2001">
Draisma 
<emphasis box="[727,779,1326,1350]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="3009">et al</emphasis>
. (2001)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="ROUSSEAU, F. &amp; BURROWES, R. &amp; PETERS, A. F. &amp; KUHLENKAMP, R. &amp; DE REVIERS, B." pageId="52" pageNumber="3009" pagination="305 - 319" refId="ref36882" refString="ROUSSEAU, F., BURROWES, R., PETERS, A. F., KUHLENKAMP, R. and DE REVIERS, B., 2001, A comprehensive phylogeny of the Phaeophyceae based on nrDNA sequences resolves earliest divergences, Comptes Rendus de l'Academie des Sciences Paris, Sciences de la Vie, 324, 305 - 319." type="journal article" year="2001">
Rousseau 
<emphasis box="[1056,1108,1326,1350]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="3009">et al</emphasis>
. (2001)
</bibRefCitation>
reveal that 
<taxonomicName box="[376,508,1358,1382]" class="Phaeophyceae" family="Asteronemataceae" genus="Asteronema" kingdom="Chromista" order="Scytothamnales" pageId="52" pageNumber="3009" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[376,508,1358,1382]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="3009">Asteronema</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is polyphyletic and not related to the 
<taxonomicName authority="Sensu" authorityName="Sensu" class="Phaeophyceae" kingdom="Chromista" order="Ectocarpales" pageId="52" pageNumber="3009" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="order">
Ectocarpales 
<emphasis box="[159,224,1390,1414]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="3009">Sensu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis box="[236,279,1390,1414]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="3009">lato</emphasis>
. Unfortunately, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ouriques and Bouzon" authorityYear="2000" baseAuthorityName="J. Agardh" box="[479,805,1390,1414]" class="Phaeophyceae" family="Asteronemataceae" genus="Asteronema" kingdom="Chromista" order="Scytothamnales" pageId="52" pageNumber="3009" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="breviarticulatum">
<emphasis box="[479,805,1390,1414]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="3009">Asteronema breviarticulatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
itself was not included in the analysis. Pending further studies, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ouriques and Bouzon" authorityYear="2000" baseAuthorityName="J. Agardh" box="[632,857,1421,1445]" class="Phaeophyceae" family="Asteronemataceae" genus="Asteronema" kingdom="Chromista" order="Scytothamnales" pageId="52" pageNumber="3009" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="breviarticulatum">
<emphasis box="[632,857,1421,1445]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="3009">A. breviarticulatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is listed as 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="3009">Incertae sedis</emphasis>
rather than under 
<taxonomicName box="[441,590,1453,1477]" class="Phaeophyceae" kingdom="Chromista" order="Ectocarpales" pageId="52" pageNumber="3009" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="order">Ectocarpales</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
